==Indonesian==
{{wikipedia|lang=id}}
===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|id|ja|焼き鳥|tr=[[やきとり]], yakitori|}}, from {{m|ja|焼き|tr=yaki|t=grilled, toasted}} + {{m|ja|鳥|tr=tori|t=bird}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|id|/ja.ki.to.ri/}}
* {{hyphenation|id|ya|ki|to|ri}}
===Noun===
{{id-noun|}}
# {{lang|en|yakitori}}, a Japanese [[shish kebab]]-type dish made with small pieces of chicken, fish, vegetables or beef which have been marinated in soy sauce and then cooked on skewers.
